cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

This paper deals with the problem of fine-grained recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a novel attention localization scheme that utilizes reinforcement learning algorithms, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of attribute descriptions, which is a common technique in natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the experimental results involve the use of a dataset, which is a common theme in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
